cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the use of blockchain technology for data provenance in IoT, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). It also involves the management and storage of data (cs.DB), as well as the design and implementation of a framework (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of smart contracts (cs.DC) and the need for efficient search and retrieval of provenance data (cs.IR).
